S. thomasiifolium

the leaves are imbricate with relatively short petioles, which give it a sessile appearance (mainly in older plants; 
Fig. 3F
); the leaf blades are cordate and covered in simple- and stellateglandular trichomes and simple-eglandular ones (the latter less conspicuous; 
